- content_for :title, "Your subscriptions"
- set_meta_tags description: "Keep an eye on the policies that matter to you"

%h2 Your subscriptions

%p.lead
  Keep an eye on the policies that matter to you

.row
  .col-md-8
    - if @user.policies_watched.any?
      %p You have subscribed to recieve emails whenever the following policies or their related divisions are updated.
      %ul
        - @user.policies_watched.each do |policy|
          %li= link_to capitalise_initial_character(policy.name_with_for), policy
      %p To unsubscribe, visit the Policy page and click <em>Unsubscribe</em>.
    - else
      %p Get email alerts whenever the policies that interest you are updated or voted on. Subscribe on the policyâ€™s page.

    =link_to "View all policies", policies_path, class: 'btn btn-default btn-sm'
